7. Ad-hoc promotion to the rank of Under Secretary to such officers subject to the following conditions:
It is -
(a) .This ad-hoc promotion is on a very temporary basis in the cadre of Under-Secretary in the Department of Ministries.
Page 4 of 7
table_trans: This ad-hoc promotion has been granted in the public interest as an administrative urgency to the posts that have been Ratted as officers of the Under Secretary cadre of the Ministry have gone on deputation in a very temporary manner.
This ad-hoc promotion will not entitle the officers concerned to any rights of regular promotion i.e. seniority.
The ad-hoc promotion will be for a period of 11 months from the date of joining of the officer / employee who has left on deputation or the order of promotion, whichever is earlier.

These ad-hoc TMAs are being issued subject to demotion of the junior-most officer / staff of this order in case there is no vacancy available in the Under Secretary cadre for senior officers / staff on deputation in the Under Secretary cadre on their repatriation.
The ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision of the Special Leave Petition No. ID1 filed in the Supreme Court.

This ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision of the High Court, Bombay in the pending Writ Petition K र.3310/2021 and Writ Petition K र.3311/2021 in आय.ए.क ID5 > and 1855/2021 as well as Writ Petition K र.3312/2021.
The ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision in the pending original Application No. र.488/2017 (Mr. Keran Jadhav et al.) at the Maharashtra Administrative Tribunal, Mumbai.

This ad-hoc promotion is being made subject to the final decision to be taken in the pending Original Application No. 1066/2019 (Mr. Ulhas Shankar Bhote et al.) at the Maharashtra Administrative Tribunal, Mumbai.

This ad-hoc promotion is being made in pursuance of the Divyang reservation, subject to change as per the procedure to be followed as provided in the General Administration Department Jashan Decision D. 29.07.2024.
